-- South Africa Beats Pakistan by Innings to Sweep Cricket Series
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2013-02-24T16:58:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-24/south-africa-beats-pakistan-by-innings-to-sweep-cricket-series.html
South Africa defeated Pakistan by an
innings and 18 runs on the third day of the final cricket Test
to sweep the series 3-0.  South Africa totaled 409 runs, with 121 from AB de Villiers
at Centurion. Visitors Pakistan then slumped to 156 all out,
Kyle Abbott taking 7-29.  Abbott took 2-39 and Dale Steyn had figures of 4-80 as
Pakistan, following on, was all out for 235.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Christopher Elser  at   celser@bloomberg.net . 